[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying static initializers**\n\nI need to look into setting a static initializer for a property. I'm wondering if any static field is of type `JavaObjectSerializer`. The nested `ConfiguredSerializer` implements `JavaObjectSerializer`, but it seems it doesn't load the `JdbcUtils` maybe? I'm also considering whether `SysProperties` could be initialized by H2. This seems like a complex relationship between these components, and I want to make sure I’ve got everything lined up correctly!\n\n**Considering test setup options**\n\nI'm thinking about using `@BeforeAll` with `System.setProperty` in the H2Test to set the property before DriverManager is utilized. But I'm wrestling with whether modifying an unrelated test is the best approach. Maybe I can add a static block in H2Test to set the property instead. That could be a broader solution without directly affecting the existing test structure. Just trying to weigh the pros and cons here!\n\n**Evaluating JVM behavior**\n\nI'm considering the JVM test run where `clinit` uses reflection for nested serializers and records, which seems good. But, if I'm under a native image, the system property specifies the nested class name containing `$`. It includes test classes, which is fine. However, I need to think about whether the user's code filter will exclude test packages. I guess it would be wise to read more about that and clarify any related issues.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_063f40c823398bca0169f91289de64819eb71910388fcfcdf3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-RKcoYXDtOSv1yRb7Dhi9rQxRK9JZRnvwKJIsg0ZPQiryFaOMjeR6hVrJV_DaXhtz9uA-e6xkzcyj-MxGR-SEXfuPa88kYZK1AO_fWHJKoKcn1eLSWFKq5XK6R2NwL7YaqgOUCNMVvR6VpO6wWZPbGkk_zIgfsDniJ-h-9_nOvZcBOkvd9uULJqkAH2ksFEvddEJejPz0bzpHNNgAJKxsNlKmFsHaq5bsdDK57gdzrdWx5Ij-OQU1TG_J6Il3BJcENp307s98FI02Rkazor4wsLY-DD9J_vu0zIlopwd9oCHVrGxq2YH4GxfHotVQovWhRNVJeBCl