ads first, the property gets set only for that test. I’m wondering if this would be limited to just that active class. It's a bit tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test class structure**\\n\\nI’m wondering about the H2Test class and its setup. Is there a one-to-one rule here? I’m thinking of adding a separate test suite class that loads before executing, but I’m not so sure about how JUnit loads test classes and executes tests. There might be a reflection-based loading mechanism at play, and I need to check if it initializes static initializers correctly. I’ll also look into build properties and the TCK plugin for more clarity.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_HHMZSdnMNwrHkxggVG0Y79dK|fc_063f40c823398bca0169f912d79740819e8ef5fe442741f382", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"systemProperty '.*'|runtimeArgs|javaObjectSerializer|nativeTest\" tests/src -g build.gradle | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 609, "output": 1201, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25874, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777930948635, "responseId": "resp_063f40c823398bca0169f912c55de8819ebcbacacfa617a746"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_HHMZSdnMNwrHkxggVG0Y79dK|fc_063f40c823398bca0169f912d79740819e8ef5fe442741f382", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.jline/jline/3.21.0/build.gradle:tasks.named(\"nativeTest\") {\ntests/src/org.apache-extras.beanshell/bsh/2.0b6/build.gradle:            runtimeArgs(\"-Djava.home=${System.getenv('JAVA_HOME')}\")\ntests/src/org.apache-extras.beanshell/bsh/2.0b6/build.gradle:            runtimeArgs(\"-Djava.class.path=${sourceSets.test.runtimeClasspath.asPath}\")\ntests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-configuration-processor/2.7.18/build.gradle:            runtimeArgs(\"-Djava.ho